cannot do it today?

00:45:19.110 --> 00:45:24.210
BRUCE FLATT: So our
general strategy

00:45:24.210 --> 00:45:29.640
is to either buy for value
when other people aren't

00:45:29.640 --> 00:45:31.150
going to that investment.

00:45:31.150 --> 00:45:34.170
And I'd say the number one
thing today with respect

00:45:34.170 --> 00:45:37.020
to retail is that retail
is one of the more

00:45:37.020 --> 00:45:40.960
heated sectors in investing
today in the world.

00:45:40.960 --> 00:45:44.310
Everyone thinks that
everything will be sold online

00:45:44.310 --> 00:45:48.330
and street retail
won't be the place.

00:45:48.330 --> 00:45:52.470
So one of the reasons
we're buying it is that.

00:45:52.470 --> 00:45:57.810
Second, we often try to operate
things better than others.

00:45:57.810 --> 00:46:00.780
With respect to GGP, I'm
not sure that's the case.

00:46:00.780 --> 00:46:04.450
They have a first class
operating platform.

00:46:04.450 --> 00:46:07.350
In fact, we'll be
adopting that platform.

00:46:07.350 --> 00:46:10.020
But the real value
that we see in that

00:46:10.020 --> 00:46:13.680
is something that can't be done
within a retail real estate

00:46:13.680 --> 00:46:15.030
company.

00:46:15.030 --> 00:46:17.550
And that's that these are--

00:46:17.550 --> 00:46:21.630
what it owns is a
125 100-acre parcels

00:46:21.630 --> 00:46:26.550
of land in the middle of each
of the cities in the United

00:46:26.550 --> 00:46:29.520
States, in major cities
in the United States.

00:46:29.520 --> 00:46:35.160
And those acreages
can be developed

00:46:35.160 --> 00:46:36.430
into many, many other things.

00:46:36.430 --> 00:46:38.760
And we have the skills
to be able to add

00:46:38.760 --> 00:46:41.790
multi-family apartments and
condominiums and storage

00:46:41.790 --> 00:46:45.120
and industrial and other
uses to those sites, which

00:46:45.120 --> 00:46:46.500
couldn't be done within GGP.

00:46:46.500 --> 00:46:48.159
And we do all
those other things.

00:46:48.159 --> 00:46:49.950
So that's really with
a value add that will

00:46:49.950 --> 00:46:51.892
bring to this acquisition.

00:46:55.356 --> 00:46:56.480
AUDIENCE: Thank you, Bruce.

00:46:56.480 --> 00:46:59.240
Thanks for the insightful
discussion today.

00:46:59.240 --> 00:47:01.580
I work for Google's
data centers.

00:47:01.580 --> 00:47:06.170
And I wanted to congratulate
