00:47:13.070 --> 00:47:17.380
is data centers have really
become an asset class in itself

00:47:17.380 --> 00:47:19.760
within the TMD space.

00:47:19.760 --> 00:47:23.840
But Brookfield is a little
late to the party, I believe.

00:47:23.840 --> 00:47:29.340
What do you think is the
hypothesis for data centers

00:47:29.340 --> 00:47:31.440
being an asset class in itself?

00:47:31.440 --> 00:47:33.990
And what would be
some of the risks

00:47:33.990 --> 00:47:37.860
that you think in acquiring a
data center like an AT&amp;T data

00:47:37.860 --> 00:47:40.380
center.

00:47:40.380 --> 00:47:42.720
BRUCE FLATT: OK,
so first, this is

00:47:42.720 --> 00:47:46.110
an amateur talking to an
expert about data centers.

00:47:46.110 --> 00:47:48.900
So I'm not sure what
advice I can give you.

00:47:48.900 --> 00:47:53.130
But I would say back to the
question on what mistakes

00:47:53.130 --> 00:47:55.710
did we have over the years,
not getting into technology.

00:47:55.710 --> 00:47:59.850
We're the largest real
estate owner in the planet.

00:47:59.850 --> 00:48:01.170
We don't own data centers.

00:48:01.170 --> 00:48:03.550
And we probably should have
been in data centers before.

00:48:03.550 --> 00:48:05.110
And if we had focused
more on technology,

00:48:05.110 --> 00:48:06.200
we would have been there.

00:48:06.200 --> 00:48:09.180
Look, I guess what
I would say broadly

00:48:09.180 --> 00:48:15.780
is we think the sector of
delivery of data infrastructure

00:48:15.780 --> 00:48:19.140
to people is we're not late.

00:48:19.140 --> 00:48:23.490
This is going to be-- the growth
of the data infrastructure

00:48:23.490 --> 00:48:26.730
sector over the next 15,
20 years as more and more

00:48:26.730 --> 00:48:30.230
data is delivered is going
to be very significant.

00:48:30.230 --> 00:48:35.010
And between fiber to
the home, data centers,

00:48:35.010 --> 00:48:36.600
and all of that,
that whole sector,

00:48:36.600 --> 00:48:39.930
we think there's enormous
amounts of capital that

00:48:39.930 --> 00:48:41.170
need to be deployed in there.

00:48:41.170 --> 00:48:46.245
And so we're just we're getting
smarter within those sectors.

