approach to the management

00:50:05.670 --> 00:50:09.250
of those assets?

00:50:09.250 --> 00:50:12.170
What's your thought
process within that?

00:50:12.170 --> 00:50:16.590
BRUCE FLATT: Yes, so
our businesses, we

00:50:16.590 --> 00:50:19.950
have 1,500 investment people.

00:50:19.950 --> 00:50:22.590
But then there's 75,000,
80,000 people down

00:50:22.590 --> 00:50:24.200
below that operate the assets.

00:50:24.200 --> 00:50:27.340
So most of the things we
do we actively operate.

00:50:27.340 --> 00:50:33.660
And we're doing things
with all those people

00:50:33.660 --> 00:50:34.830
once we buy an asset.

00:50:34.830 --> 00:50:37.470
Sometimes we adopt the people,
and we're integrating them

00:50:37.470 --> 00:50:39.360
into our business.

00:50:39.360 --> 00:50:43.050
Once in a while we're
just a financial investor

00:50:43.050 --> 00:50:45.120
into something because
somebody brought us in

00:50:45.120 --> 00:50:47.820
and the reason for us to come in
was that we could provide them

00:50:47.820 --> 00:50:48.750
capital.

00:50:48.750 --> 00:50:51.240
But most things we
do are quite active.

00:50:51.240 --> 00:50:54.810
And we think the lion's
share of the return we get

00:50:54.810 --> 00:50:56.460
isn't from a
financial return, it's

00:50:56.460 --> 00:51:02.860
from an asset intensive return
by operating assets better.

